  <title>Set up automatic suspend</title>

  <p>You can configure your computer to automatically suspend when idle.
  Different intervals can be specified for running on battery or plugged in.</p>

  <steps>

    <item>
      <p>Atveriet <gui xref="shell-introduction#activities">Aktivitāšu</gui> pārskatu un sāciet rakstīt <gui>Barošana</gui>.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Spiediet <gui>Barošana</gui>, lai atvērtu paneli.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>In the <gui>Suspend &amp; Power Button</gui> section, click
      <gui>Automatic suspend</gui>.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Choose <gui>On Battery Power</gui> or <gui>Plugged In</gui>, set the
      switch to <gui>ON</gui>, and select a <gui>Delay</gui>. Both options can
      be configured.</p>

      <note style="tip">
        <p>On a desktop computer, there is one option labeled
        <gui>When Idle</gui>.</p>
      </note>
    </item>

  </steps>

